The systems main purpose is to reduce felt recoil by 30%. There are two functions that happen when the system engages, the primary impulse begins to travel the brass piece rearwards and the secondary impulse begins to travel the follower rearward and the two meet and cancel each other out. postcontent: This is a first series pistol made in 1952. Serial number is 66782. This revolver has the early wrap around grips. The box is in fair condition. I am not the first owner of the revolver, however I have known the person who owned it before me for over 35 years and if he tells me he never fired it once, he never fired it once. I also took it to a 25 year long gunsmith for evaluation and the gun is in its original condition and not one bullet was chambered in it. When you see it, you will know exactly what we are talking about. The grips are just as perfect with absolutely no damage, scratches, nicks, etc. This style of grip was only used for a very short time before switching to the slab sided ones. The blue finish would rate 99%+ condition. This is as nice as it gets for a first series Colt match revolver. In this early model, the .22 LR Caliber model is fairly rare. This is a HIGHLY collectable model and would be a top billed addition to anyone’s boxed Colt collection.Now I was at the Tulsa Gun Show this past weekend and there were a few of this model of Colt, but they were 3rd and two 4th issue ones.  They were going for between 1100 and 1800 dollars.  Since mine is a 1st issue and in new condition, I will only accept offers that reflect the quality and value of this Colt, regarding a cash price.  I am interested in a possible trade, but only for a FN 5.7, Colt Python, Colt Diamondback (only the stainless models) or a Springfield 1911 EMP.  Also might be interested in something I may not be thinking about, as long as it is in the price range.  Let me know if you have any questions.
